HEADWORD: Postgeniture
<hw>Post*gen"i*ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>post-</ets> + L. <ets>genitura</ets> birth, geniture.]</ety>
<def>The condition of being born after another in the same family; --
distinguished from <xex>primogeniture</xex>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

